### `deal_room/rewards/utterance_scorer.py` — ✅ Working

Pure Python. Zero LLM. Zero cache. All 13 unit tests passing.

```python
LOOKAHEAD_COST = 0.07   # single definition — all other files import from here
LOG2_6 = np.log2(6)
```

Five dimension formulas (all computed from `StateSnapshot` delta):

| Dim | Formula | Center |
|-----|---------|--------|
| goal | `0.50×approval_Δ + 0.30×blocker_Δ + 0.20×veto_headroom_Δ` | 0.5 |
| trust | `0.6×positive_mass_Δ + 0.4×trustworthy_mass_Δ` for targeted | 0.5 |
| info | `mean(H_before_i − H_after_i) / LOG2_6` over all stakeholders | 0.5 |
| risk | `mean((CVaR_before − CVaR_after) / CVaR_before)` for λ>0.30 | 0.5 |
| causal | `betweenness_centrality(target, G) / max_centrality(G)` | 0–1 |

Lookahead: `if lookahead_used or action.lookahead is not None: goal = max(0, goal - 0.07)`.

Aggregation: `score.weighted_sum(REWARD_WEIGHTS)` — weighted, not `/5.0`.

